///
/// Introduction
@node "Introduction"

  INTRODUCTION:
  =============

  Some day ago, iÇve got the following problem:
  IÇve recorded many short scenes with movieshop. This is not really a problem, but
  IÇve forgotten to turn off the audio-recording within movieshop. So all scenes got
  the o-soundtrack, which wasnÇt needed by me.

  So I could choose to kill the project and do all recordings again (without the aound)
  or to remove the sound from every scene.
  I said: NO !!!  There must be an esier way to do that... And there was an easier way...

  So this program was born - I just named it ÇSound-KillerÇ.

@endnode
