///
/// Installation
@node "Installation"

  INSTALLATION:
  =============

  Because the day only got 24 hours (better were 60...80 hours ;-))), there will be no
  script for the commodoreÇs installer. You have to copy the files Çby handÇ. But this
  will be no problem, because all files and drawers are included in the archive.


  How to copy:
  ============

  Decrunch the archive - by using the lha - to any drawer (the best is the RAM: disk).
  If you donÇt know how to use the lha, hereÇs a short description (the archive must be
  in RAM: and the lha-command must be in C:):


  - open a shell-window.
  - change the current drawer to RAM: using the ÇCD RAM:Ç-command.
  - enter the following command: LHA X ARCHIVE.LHA   (ARCHIVE.LHA muste be the name
    of the program-archive).
    The decrunched files you will find in the RAM:-disk, too.
  - Copy all files of the decrunched drawer to your Ç...movieshop/macrosÇ-drawer using the
    command: COPY FALCONÇS_MS-TOOLS TO .../MOVIESHOP/MACROS ALL.
    Ç.../MOVIESHOP...Ç means your installation-path of movieshop. If your movieshop is
    installed on DH2: in the drawer VIDEO, the command will be:
    COPY FALCONÇS_MS-TOOLS TO DH2:VIDEO/MOVIESHOP/MACROS ALL

    If you donÇt want to see the output-window generated by the ÇcopyÇ-command, just add
    the option ÇQUIETÇ at the end of the commandline.


    After the installation, you should find the following drawers into your movieshop/macros-
    drawer:


    ... MOVIESHOP/MACROS/FALCONÇS_MS-TOOLS/EXE
    ...     "       "       "       "     /HELP
    ...     "       "       "       "     /KEYFILES
    ...     "       "       "       "     /PREFS
    ...     "       "       "       "     /LOCALE         


   NOTE: To use your favorite language, just copy the used GUIDE-file into the ÇHELPÇ-drawer.
         With the programfile, just do the same.


  ====================================================================================================


  PROGRAM-LAUNCHER:
  =================

  Simply you could just copy all my ms-tools to your macros-drawer, do that. If my programs
  will not find the above said paths, they will search in different paths to find the used
  files (fonts, prefs, ...):

  ... MOVIESHOP/MACROS        ===>  Here will be looked for keyfiles, guides and prefsfiles.
  ... MOVIESHOP               ===>  Keyfiles, guides and prefs will be found here, too.
  ... MOVIESHOP/HELP/DEUTSCH  ===>  Guide-files are found here, if not on other places found.
  ENVARC:MOVIESHOP            ===>  Only prefsfiles will be searched here, if not found anywhere else.


  IÇve written a program-launcher, because:

  - you can enter only a view of programs and scripts here. Only my own programs are more than
    the menu can take.
  - all my ms-tools are together in one drawer. If you want to update someting, you just have
    to exchange the old file with the new file... and it works.



  INSTALLATION OF THE PROGRAM-LAUNCHER:
  =====================================

  At the moment, there will be only a german version of this program. If I can get some time,
  I will write an english version, too.

  - At first copy the file ÇFALCONÇs MS-ToolsÇ to your ÇmacrosÇ-drawer.
  - Open the ÇmacrosÇ-window of your movieshop and click at the ÇNEWÇ-button.
    With the button ÇALIAS/SCRIPTÇ you select ÇSCRIPTÇ.
  - Klick at the button ÇAUSWAHLÇ and choose the file ÇFalconÇs MS-ToolsÇ by using the
    filerequester. The last line into the window will contain ÇMACROS/FalconÇs MS-ToolsÇ.
    If not, please select the ÇDELETEÇ-button and try again.
  - Insert a name for the program-launcher (MS-Tools) into the first line of the window.
  - If you want to start it by using a hotkey, type the hotkey into the second line.
  - Set the ÇmenuÇ-mark to start it from the ÇmacrosÇ-menu, too.
  - Use the save-function to store the settings to your harddisk.
  - Close the window.
  - READY. Now you can start all MS-tools by using the program-launcher.

@endnode
///
/// Usage
@node "Usage"

  USAGE:
  =====

  - First open a movieshop-project.
  - Create a scenegroup and put there all scenes you want to remove the soundtrack.
    If this group includes other groups, this groups will not be changed.
  - Run the sound-killer with the program-launcher or by selecting from the
    ÇmacrosÇ-menu.

    NOTE: You can stop all functions by closing the scenes-window from movieshop.
          The program will ask you to exit or to continue.

    Fist the program calculates the number of scenes and scenegroups. If the number
    of scenes is calculated, the program will ask you to remove the soundtracks.

    Now, the program begins to work. If you want to stop it, just close the scene-
    window from movieshop. If you stop, all scenes after the current calculated
    scene will keep teir soundtracks.

    All calculated scenes will get the scenenote ÇSoundtrack removed.Ç.
@endnode
