///
/// More stuff
@node "More stuff"

  More stuff:
  ===========

  At this time (december 1999) you can find the following tools on my homepage:


  MOVIESHOP:
  ----------

              Compare: Compares the timeline-contents with the scenes of the scenes-
                       window.

            JPEG-Rate: Calculates the transferrate of your videostream and shows it
                       with 2d- and 3d-graphicoutput. Includes an arexx-port.

           Sortscenes: Allows you to sort all your scenes by alphabetic order.


        Show-Position: Shows you the scene-position as framenumber and time.


        MovieSFX-Tool: With this tool you can transfer samples between movieshop
                       and SoundFX. Only requirement: A lot of diskspace...

            Moviehack: A hack to show the paloma-tv picture on the movieshop-screen.

         Correct-Sync: This program solves an error from movieshop 4.8 / 4.9b7.
                       If you playback your video, sometimes the video and audio
                       will not be synchron after playing some time.

    Also on my homepage: Operators and timelines and many other stuff...



    SOUNDFX:
    --------

    Channel-Converter: Converts mono- <==> mtereo- <==> quattro-samples.

     Channel-Switcher: Turns any sample-channel pon/off.

                 Info: Replacement for the original Info-script.

              MOD2SFX: Converts a lot of MOD-file formats into samples and
                       puts them to your movieshop audio-partition.

              SFX2MP3: This program is under construction, now. It will
                       convert any sample to the mp3-format by using the
                       freeware encoder ÇNCODEÇ.


  On my homepage you will find all used libraries and programs.


  HAVE A LOOK ...


@endnode
